com.vicinityconcepts.lib.util

Class Caller

  • java.lang.Object
    • com.vicinityconcepts.lib.util.Caller

  • public class Caller
extends java.lang.Object
    Simple data structure to store information about calling code, including class name, method name, and line number.
    Author:
    Ryan Palmer

    • Method Detail

      • infer

        public static Caller infer(java.lang.String currentClass)
                    throws CallerNotFoundException
        Infer the caller by searching the stack trace for the first element outside of the specified current class name.
        Parameters:
        currentClass - The name of the current class.
        Returns:
        a new Caller based on the inferred calling code.
        Throws:
        CallerNotFoundException - if the calling code could not be inferred.

      • rewind

        public static Caller rewind(int steps)
                     throws CallerNotFoundException
        Get the caller by reading a previous stack trace element. Useful as a fallback if automatically inferring the caller is unsuccessful.
        Parameters:
        steps - Number of times to step backwards through the stack trace.
        Returns:
        a new Caller based on the calling code.
        Throws:
        CallerNotFoundException - if the rewind exceeds the size of the stack trace.

      • unknown

        public static Caller unknown()
        Get a caller without any useful information. Can be used when inferring and rewinding both fail, but you still need to pass along some kind of caller object.
        Returns:
        a new Caller with default values representing unknown calling code.
